  "texts": [
    "Then, the chemical collision frequencies (ν CH i) 1≤i≤4given by (34) should be controlled by their elastic counterparts (ν EL i) 1≤i≤4 given by (8), through the additional condition: (CH5) There exists a constant β CH > 0 such that, for any 1 ≤ i ≤ 4, it holdsν CH i (v) ≤ β CH ν EL i (v), ∀v ∈ R 3.At last, as pointed out above, we must make sure that micro-reversibility holds.",
    "Because of (CH4), this is verified as soon as:(CH6) The functions Φ hk ij satisfy condition (14), namelygΦ hk ij (g) = m hk m ij 2 g hk ij Φ ij hk (g hk ij), ∀v, v * ∈ R 3.Like with the elastic case, the additional hypothesis (CH5) essentially translates a property of equivalence between chemical and elastic collision frequencies, ensuring that the spectral gap of L EL can be used to control the Dirichlet form of L CH.",
    "Here, we chose to follow a simpler approach by considering the slightly more restrictive condition (CH3), in place of (CH3')-(CH5)-(CH6), to guarantee that ν CH i (v) ∼ ν EL i (v) ∼ 1 + |v| γ for any 1 ≤ i ≤ 4= v-v * |v-v * |, one can apply standard changes of variable (v, v *, σ) → (v ′, v ′ *, κ) and (v, v *, σ) → (v *, v, -σ) to prove that the operators Q EL i (F, F) satisfy the weak formulation (15)4 i=1 R 3 Q EL i (F, F)(v)ψ i (v)dv = - 1 4 4 i=1 4 j=1 R 6 ×S 2 B ij (|v -v * |, cos θ) F ′ i F ′ * j -F i F * j × ψ i (v ′) + ψ j (v ′ *) -ψ i (v) -ψ j (v *) dv * dvdσ.The micro-reversibilities satisfied by the chemical component used in tandem with a combination of changes of variables of the form (v, v *, σ)→ (v hk ij, v hk * ij, κ) and (v, v *, σ) → (v *, v, -σ), dependingon the combinations of indices (i, j, h, k), allows to argue in a similar way [37] that the operators Q CH i (F, F) satisfy the weak formulation ( 16)4 i=1 R 3 Q CH i (F, F)(v)ψ i (v)dv = - R 6 ×S 2 H |v -v * | 2 - 2E 34 12 m 12 B 34 12 (|v -v * |, cos θ) × m 12 m 34 3 F 3 (v ′)F 4 (v ′ *) -F 1 (v)F 2 (v *) ψ 3 (v ′) + ψ 4 (v ′ *) -ψ 1 (v) -ψ 2 (v *) dv * dvdσ,where v ′ = v 34 12 and v ′ * = v 34 * 12 are the reference post-collisional velocities of the reaction S 1 + S 2 ⇋ S 3 + S 4, being the sole needed to characterize the conservation laws associated with Q CH.",
    "Additionally, for the chemical operator it is also possible to prove [47] that its components satisfy the following fundamental mass-conservation laws (17)R 3 Q CH 1 (F, F)(v)dv = R 3 Q CH 2 (F, F)(v)dv = - R 3 Q CH 3 (F, F)(v)dv = - R 3 Q CH 4 (F, F)(v)dv.Combining the weak formulations ( 15) and ( 16), one deduces the conservation properties of the multi-species reactive Boltzmann operator Q.",
    "More precisely, using the microscopic conservation of momentum and energy satisfied by the elastic collisions (7) and by the chemical reactions (12), the conservation properties of Q are given by4 i=1 R 3 Q EL i (F, F)(v)ψ i (v)dv = 0, 4 i=1 R 3 Q CH i (F, F)(v)ψ i (v)dv = 0,(18)and these equalities hold simultaneously if and only if ψ ψ ψ is a collision invariant of the reactive mixture, namelyψ ψ ψ ∈ Span e 13, e 14, e 24, v 1 m, v 2 m, v 3 m, 1 2 |v| 2 m + E,where we have denoted e 13 = (1, 0, 1, 0), e 14 = (1, 0, 0, 1), e 24 = (0, 1, 0, 1), m = (m 1,..., m 4) and E = (E 1,..., E 4)."
